<div id="review_1245526171" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1245526171" />
    <a title="Pamela " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3925721-pamela"><img alt="Pamela " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1386249684p2/3925721.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1245526171?book_show_action=true">Apr 04, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Pamela " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Pamela " href="/user/show/3925721-pamela">Pamela </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3925721-pamela?shelf=kindle">kindle</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3925721-pamela?shelf=reviewed">reviewed</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer1245526171&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1245526171" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer926050999192681447"><br/><br/><b>
  <i>2.5 stars</i>
</b><br/><br/>For a novel that started off really well, one with an intriguing story that sucks you in right from the start, I couldn’t believe how quickly it took a nosedive at the half-way mark only to crash and burn. I really liked both Grey and Gloria. I loved his story how, by chance, Grey was able to get a second chance at a new life with the help and kindness of a woman who saw the good in him. Then there’s Barb, who’s been mentally and physically abused for years at the hands of her husba</span>
  <span id="freeText926050999192681447" style="display:none"><br /><br /><b>
  <i>2.5 stars</i>
</b><br /><br />For a novel that started off really well, one with an intriguing story that sucks you in right from the start, I couldn’t believe how quickly it took a nosedive at the half-way mark only to crash and burn. I really liked both Grey and Gloria. I loved his story how, by chance, Grey was able to get a second chance at a new life with the help and kindness of a woman who saw the good in him. Then there’s Barb, who’s been mentally and physically abused for years at the hands of her husband, who wants to escape so she and her daughter can have a better life. With both Grey and Barb, you could actually feel the pain they were going thru. <br /><br />With the help of some women, Barb’s been planning to leave her husband and disappear with her child, and after a year of planning she finally had the chance. At this point I’ve reached the half-way mark and this is where, in my opinion, it started to fall apart for me. When a woman who’s being physically and mentally abused by her husband wishes to leave and disappear, that’s what they do. They DISAPPEAR. What they don’t do is disappear to grandma’s house. Barb’s year of planning was so she could accumulate enough money to leave and live comfortably. Fine. I totally get it. However, the story doesn’t work if you go to grandma and then have her pay for everything. Which brings me to wonder why wait a whole year to leave? Why would you have a woman be your double, take your place on a flight booked under your name, and you take a different flight to grandma’s? Your job requires you to travel several times a year so why not just leave then? Your husband knows you take these business trips and has never stopped you. Hell, he takes business trips too, sometimes for days. You could’ve left at any time. All of this (body-double, sneaking around, planning) seems to be a waste because you’re going to GRANDMA’s place. Your husband knows you have a grandma. She was at your wedding. He knows where grandma lives. How is this hiding?? (Major eye rolls happening.) <br /><br />When Barb and Grey meet, there’s an immediate attraction. I totally get this as this is part of the story. What I don’t get is when after years of suffering abuse from you husband, and within a couple of days of showing up at grandma’s, Barb is making advances on Grey, kissing and touching him. Of course he reciprocates. They kiss and make out. I’m sorry but this doesn’t come across as realistic. Yes, this is fiction, but can we at least make is somewhat realistic. How about taking care of yourself and your daughter and taking the time to gather your thoughts, deal with what you went thru? Not see a man and starting salivating and dreaming of being underneath him. Even the events that take place, which includes her husband, I found it all ridiculous; not to mention it was wrapped up too quickly. After all the hype of what her ex was going to do to her, it all fell flat. For a novel that started off well, I have to say I was quite peeved the direction it took. Hence, 2.5 stars. <br /><br />*Please note: My opinions with respect to this novel is just that, my opinions. However, if anyone feels that I’m way off base or I don’t have a clear understanding when it comes to an abused women, I don’t mind discussing it with you. My review is not meant to hurt, disrespect, or make light of anyone with respect to this subject matter. </span>
  <a data-text-id="926050999192681447" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

