<div id="review_1240502594" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1240502594" />
    <a title="Tatiana Lammers" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4387613-tatiana-lammers"><img alt="Tatiana Lammers" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1354872286p2/4387613.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1240502594?book_show_action=true">Mar 29, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tatiana Lammers" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tatiana Lammers" href="/user/show/4387613-tatiana-lammers">Tatiana Lammers</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4387613-tatiana-lammers?shelf=beta-reading">beta-reading</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1240502594" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer482700879837566963">I read this book as a Beta version.<br/><br/>Stacy Eaton has a way of writing about tough subjects that most people either gloss over or simply skip altogether. She does not pretty it up; she just writes what needs to be said. Some parts are heart-wrenching, some anger-inducing. The book is extremely well written.<br/><br/>Although the books Stacy writes are fiction, I know that there are girls and women out in the world who can relate to what she is not afraid to write about. <br/><br/>The characters come alive in this book</span>
  <span id="freeText482700879837566963" style="display:none">I read this book as a Beta version.<br /><br />Stacy Eaton has a way of writing about tough subjects that most people either gloss over or simply skip altogether. She does not pretty it up; she just writes what needs to be said. Some parts are heart-wrenching, some anger-inducing. The book is extremely well written.<br /><br />Although the books Stacy writes are fiction, I know that there are girls and women out in the world who can relate to what she is not afraid to write about. <br /><br />The characters come alive in this book. The emotion the writer is able to elicit from her characters and pass on through her words is incredible. While some parts of this book are not for the faint of heart, I am once again glad that I had the chance to read it. This book is a very emotional read (with sad but also with happy moments). This author has a way of writing that really gets you into the book and makes you feel as if you are right there with the characters. The story is touching and powerful. The writing is masterful, with vivid and often graphic details. From the total unexpected anguish that you didn't see coming, to the bubble of hope and, finally, joy as you travel on a journey with these characters and find yourself crossing your fingers for a happy ending. A story like this sticks with you long after the last page and makes you grateful for the life you have.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="482700879837566963" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


